{"key":"processedPost-8752041","value":{"id":8752041,"first":8750832,"last":8757188,"when":1218377329,"utime":"08/10/08 05:08 PM","content":"Actually, most growers here have hydrotron left over from other projects.&nbsp; They don't replace perlite unless you want to pile them extremely deep.&nbsp; They simply don't have the surface area to evaporate water that perlite has.<br />I have three bags of hydrotron balls in my garage now.&nbsp; I've tried them with and without standing water and bubblers, and they're simply not worth the trouble.&nbsp; They're intended to provide stability to root systems, not to evaporate water off their surface.&nbsp; Rocks also won't help much.&nbsp; You want the extremely high surface area that perlite has, so once wet, it has a large area to evaporate water from.<br />RR","title":"Re: Using Hydrotron balls instead of Perlite in FC, need some help"}}